# RustDroid Daemon Init Configuration (v0.8 Android Boot Integration)
#
# This file is used to register and launch the privileged RustDroid daemon.
# Lifecycle:
# - The service starts during 'post-fs-data' trigger, ensuring that the decrypted
#   /data storage and the base folder /data/adb/rustdroid are fully decrypted and ready.
# - Running with '--foreground' is standard to let init monitor the service.
#
# Safety Scope:
# - It only launches the daemon in the legitimate, privileged system context.
# - It does not contain bypass, hiding, or stealth behavior.
# - It does not disable or weaken SELinux.
# - It does not execute systemless root pivots.
# - Module mounting is not enabled in v0.8.
# - Version v0.8 only prepares assets and launches the daemon.

on post-fs-data
    # Start the daemon when /data persistent structures are decrypted and mounted.
    start rustdroidd

service rustdroidd /data/adb/rustdroid/bin/rustdroidd --foreground
    user root
    group root
    seclabel u:r:su:s0
    oneshot
    disabled
